cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.AR. 

The paper proposes a network architecture for mobile edge computing, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses live Avatar migration and proposes a strategy to optimize the tradeoff between migration gain and cost, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The optimization strategy also involves maximizing profit, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
